15:T44b,Internal evidence clearly establishes this as a urological guidewire product family with PTFE coating. The brochure describes key clinical features: flexible atraumatic tip, excellent torquability for precise control during urological procedures. Specifications indicate 0.028-0.038 inch diameters, 150 cm length, available in straight and J-tip configurations - all consistent with standard urological guidewires. PTFE (polytetrafluoroethylene) is a hydrophobic coating material applied to metal core guidewires, not the core material itself. The core is typically stainless steel or nitinol. 'Meriskate' appears to be the product brand/trade name. However, no external verification is available, and brand attribution to Meril Life Sciences cannot be confirmed from internal evidence alone. The absence of manufacturer documentation, SKU data, or external corroboration requires review to confirm manufacturer, verify complete product specifications, and validate the product family scope. Confidence reduced to 0.75 due to unverified manufacturer attribution and lack of supporting documentation.7:["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0A0A0A] text-white","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org/\",\"@type\":\"Product\",\"name\":\"Meriskate PTFE Guidewire\",\"description\":\"Flexible tip provides atraumatic advancement. Excellent torquability for precise control and placement during urological procedures.\",\"brand\":{\"@type\":\"Brand\",\"name\":\"Meril\"},\"category\":\"Guidewires\",\"manufacturer\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Meril Life Sciences\"},\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"AggregateOffer\",\"offerCount\":\"1\",\"lowPrice\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"INR\",\"availability\":\"https://schema.org/InStock\"}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-24","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"flex mb-10 text-sm text-mute